<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-05"><hi rend="italic">September 5,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1398.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. White’s No. 2039, of the 20th ultimo,
                            has been received.</p>
                        <p>The public official explanation of the words “for police reasons” in the
                            order expelling the Eisemann brothers from Prussia appears to be what
                            the Messrs. Eisemann desired, and the incident may therefore be
                            considered closed.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>